<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>fudorf</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Dec 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><i>Originally posted by Gloobonious </i><br />
<b>Alchemy has the potential to be an extremely beneficial tradeskill. Unfortunately, Verant obviously doesn't care enough to make it that way. I just want to get some ideas out of how to make it more useful to people, and more viable to make profit for the Shaman.</b><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Depending on how you look at it, it already is, or never will be.  After a certain point in skill, you can pretty much count on a 100% profit on SoW pots.  And 30-40% on the rest of the commonly bought potions (ITU/EB/Lev/Shrink/etc).  <br />
<br />
On the other side of the coin, until the pricing on components fall more in line with the actual utility of the potion, the high end stuff will never be overall profitable.  At 54, I surely would not pay 100+ pp for a breeze, or even clarity.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><b><br />
Component-Free Utility Potions (Think the current ones require a component...): Levitate, Enduring Breath, Gate. Bind Affinity, and any others I forgot. IMHO, Bind Affinity could be one that requires a lot of extremely rare components and a maximized skill. Gaurenteed seller for tanks tired of running from cities. To sum it up, would revitalize the skill.<br />
<hr size="1" /></blockquote></b><br />
<br />
Some of these already exist, a la old world alchemy.  And they are insta-click.  We also have 2 different mod-rod style potions, among others.<br />
<br />
In my mind, it is doubtful we will ever see either a bind or craftable gate potion.  Sure, bind is nice to make a few PP off of in CB or FP, but after a while, that tank is going to start to have to group.  And any caster in that group not willing to bind at the nearest available location isn't worth having.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><b><br />
Improved Port Potions: Port to a lot of places besides the ones granted. Put in an extremely difficult potion that ports someone to the Nexus from anywhere... and there you go, a hot seller. More locations would not hurt either, besides the 3 or 4 destinations potions are currently limited to. Heck, make potions that drop you at any spire in Norrath!<br />
<br />
Offensive Potions: Anyone remember UO? Throwing potions at people was always fun. And if that doesn't seem viable, there could be other offensive aid potions. The DS is good, but there should be more. There should be a potion for a combat proc of some sort, perhaps a potion that absorbs melee damage per-hit, a SpellShield style potion, etc. IE: &quot;Potion of Flickering Flame&quot; could give you a chance to proc a fire-based 50DD each hit.<br />
<br />
Raising the skill cap for some of the newer potions would be good too (the clarity ones come to mind.) I would personally not open it up to cap at 250 until level 50, though... I've always enjoyed that only the highest-level Shamans can max Alchemy. Should keep it that way.</b><hr size="1" /></blockquote>/sarcasm on<br />
If you are going to use the UO comparison, why not just make a rune book, that is rechargable via scroll.  And usable by anyone<br />
/sarcasm off<br />
<br />
As a 54 Barbarian Shaman, from the Nexus, I can - gate to bind, gate to Thurgadin, gate to Everfrost (spiritstone), Portal to NK, DL, GFay, GD and Toxx... pretty much within reach of anywhere I need to go in a matter of 15 minutes or less.<br />
<br />
For a small donation, can be ported to any wizard or druid spot, with little effort on my part.  What more do we want, or need?  The only gate potions worth persuing are FoB and Inny... for easier access to EJ/CoM/TT/Seb, etc, or CT.  How much more convenience do we want?  How far do you want the scales of imbalance to be pushed for that convenience?<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><b><br />
I would rather have a series of great potions that are difficult to make (a'la the new tradeskilling revamp), over the current selection of easy potions to make that simply don't do anything useful to anyone. </b><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Our potions are all usable.  Beyond the damage shields, none of the high skill ones are affordable, either to make in bulk, or to sell.  I would prefer they remove the negative stats from what we have, and bring the component prices more in line with the utility of the spell itself, to make it a buyable product.</p>
	
	
	
