	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><i>Originally posted by Gloobonious </i><br />
<b>I would rather have a series of great potions that are difficult to make (a'la the new tradeskilling revamp), over the current selection of easy potions to make that simply don't do anything useful to anyone. </b><hr size="1" /></blockquote>These exist.  Try making Greater Concentration potion with maxed alchemy + Philosopher's Stone.  60% success rate.  The effect is like FT3, lasts 30 mins.<br />
<br />
Oh by the way, VI's solution to the 180 skill cap on alchemy is a real crock.  Someone had the idiotic notion to make one of the shaman class AA skills Alchemy Mastery.  Who in their right mind is going to waste 18 AA points on this stupid skill so they can make a stack of potions that cost 1800pp that no one will buy?</p>
	
	
	
