	<p>After reading the posts I must say that I agree and that I have felt the same way for some time.<br />
Why not give potions better stats at higher skill levels to get <br />
more people active in Alchemy.<br />
Other reasons I think Alchemy isn't profitable is simple, why pay for potions when you can /ooc and find someone willing to cast the buff or spell on you? I know this isn't always possible, but I think people don't look at it that way. Also I feel sow potions should be able to work indoors.<br />
Other ideas, keeping in mind shaman powers seem to stem from <br />
animals:<br />
<br />
 Potion of Playing Possum ( Feign Death )<br />
<br />
 Potion of Chameleon ( invis to all, animal, dead. npc - except ones that see invis )<br />
<br />
 Potion of Ursa Major ( the celestial bear - teleport to luclin )<br />
<br />
 Potion of the Vampire Bat ( casts the SK spell Vampric Embrace - life tap proc ) etc.<br />
