<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Mitrian</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jul 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Well, be glad we're not rogues.  Alchemy is a dream compared to a rogue's poison difficulties.  (In my opinion.)<br />
<br />
There's a couple general complaints I see about Alchemy.<br />
1.)  Too expensive for the effects.<br />
2.)  No demand for the effects.<br />
3.)  Much easier/cheaper to get the effects elsewhere.<br />
<br />
Ideally, it would be nice to have Alchemy be a tradeskill that is both profitable AND highly effective.  Unfortunately, both paths can be realized with precious few potions only (Blood of the Wolf, or Ant's Potion, for example).  Overall, though, most shamans pick one or the other (profit vs. effective potions) to pursue as an Alchemist.  One of my shaman friends absolutely LOVES alchemy as a profit machine.  His skill is only about 80 I think, but he's made a ton of money with the skill just selling the profitable/in demand potions.  (Personally I think it would be boring to make just sows, shrinks and ITU, but it's a viable option!)<br />
<br />
If Verant was going to make it both a profitable and effective skill though, a combination of some of these suggestions might work:<br />
a)  Make more potion effects be based on the level of the drinker<br />
b)  Make components cheaper (at least closer to the value of the effect)<br />
c)  Add more of the components to mob loot tables<br />
d)  Increase durations to many of the effects<br />
e)  Do away with so many of the negative effects of potions<br />
f)  Get rid of the potion vendors (i.e. I hate that people can buy heal/invis potions but we can't make them!)<br />
g)  Or at least allow us to make those potions too!<br />
h)  Add damage potions for range/ammo slot (throw a DoT or DD!)<br />
i)  I'd love to see a snare or root potion, too, but I suppose I'm dreaming.<br />
<br />
Or... just leave it the way it is.  All other tradeskills have a lot of useless (or certainly not cost-effective) items produced that no one will ever buy ~ that is certainly not unique to Alchemy.  The biggest difference is that there are high-level items in the other skills that have a market, whereas our high-level items no one will pay that much for (more than once anyway)!  i.e. 1k for 10-dose Breeze!?  Overall, the skill is a fun and useful skill once you figure it out.  It's just costly to skill up with no real quantifiable reward for having a max skill.<br />
<br />
Just my thoughts...<br />
<br />
[60 Oracle] Mitrian &lt;Emerald Flame&gt;<br />
The Seventh Hammer<br />
180 Alchemy</p>
	
	
	
	
