<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Shandy Orcbane</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Oracle<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Mar 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Stinging Wort potions are Balm Leaf (35-40p, gypsy vendors, and a vendor in SH) + Ice Giant Toes (off of--you guessed it--ice giants and Gornit).<br />
<br />
The effect is &quot;Calillimony&quot; and is +17 Str, +300hp.  It's instant-cast.  The 300 hp buff is a max-hp buff and 300hp heal (like Altuna, etc) but you start losing the extra hp capacity shortly.<br />
<br />
I've heard that it's a 300hp dot as well, but I've not looked that closely at it.  Usually I've got Regrowth on, which far outstrips the couple of hp per tick that you might lose.<br />
<br />
You can stack this on top of regen spells, but you cannot stack regen spells on top of this.<br />
<br />
I use it in 5-shots (when I can afford it) as a security blanket when I'm off soloing.  Nice having a 1500hp instant heal in your pocket.</p>
	
	
	
