<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>vaniar luclin</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jun 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>OK heres how calimony works.... I know because I carry a 10 charge on every twink I play as well as my 60 shaman. They are absolutely the GREATEST get out of a crappy situation free card EVER! They are insta cast ( IE while you run you can cast this)!<br />
<br />
One dose gives you 300 HPs on a DoT decline. This means that it raises your HP total 300 points (ex you have 2000 hps, you chug one you now have 2300 total Hps)  Immediatly you will begin to loose the added HPS at a rate of 10 HPs per tick for 5 min (at the end of the 5 min you would be back to your original 2000 HPs)<br />
<br />
The heal effect from Chugging a 5 dose comes in this way. You take the above 2000 HPs. You finish a fight at 500 HPs. You drink one dose this would raise your total Hps to 2300 and your actual health to 800. Taking another charge immediatly (before the dot decline takes effect) Will NOT raise your total HPs again but it WILL raise your health another 300 points bringing you to 2300 total but now you are at 1200 health (500 + 300 + 300). Now at this point the numbers would start to drop slightly because of the DoT decline but for the sake of the excersise we will freeze time. Chugging another potion would take you to 1500 health again with your total HPs staying at 2300. <br />
<br />
The heal comes into effect because the DoT decline ONLY effects the extra 300 hps on the total, regardless of your health.<br />
<br />
Chugging a 5 charge would give 1500 HPs (also adding 300 to your total available HPS that would be on a dot decline)<br />
<br />
SOOOoooooo your 2000 HP guy. Hes at 200 health chugs a 5 charge hes now at 1700 health with an added 300 HPs (2300 total) that will drop at 10 HPs a tick till he comes back to 2000 HPs and the effect drops. The healed HPs are NOT effected unless hes actually healed to the full 2300 then you will see hte total HPs drop slowly but hes not damaged, hes just loosing the total possible.<br />
<br />
Theres How Calimony works <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Van x 6<br><br />
Luclin<br><br />
