	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>(On the other side of the coin, until the pricing on components fall more in line with the actual utility of the potion, the high end stuff will never be overall profitable. At 54, I surely would not pay 100+ pp for a breeze, or even clarity. )<br />
<br />
But we will gladly pay 100 pp for KEI.  Verant gives enchanters a 40000 pp spell that pays for itself in a weekend, but gives shaman the dream of a useful potion, but at the exact same time destroys the market for them.  Gotta love Verant and their even handed treatment of classes.<br />
<br />
I have a suggestion however.  Give us a spell that when casts gives us a quantity of herbs off the alchemy table.  usable only outdoors of course. Different herbs found in different zones like with druids and foraging.  In effect this would be a casting based forage for items.  Its not like shamanic peoples dont go looking for their herbs.  Before Verant has a fit, remember that we dont get any real money selling the potions back as it is now so if we blow our mana for an herb off the table, we certainly wont be destroying the market with a flood of cheap potions.  The mana would be more profitably used to hunt but this has posibilities. <br />
This spell is more thematic but would give us a downtime way to help our hobby.<br />
<br />
If implemented, I would have a successful casting yield more of the herb based on the level of the caster.  Like you found a patch of wild ______).  At L60 you find 20, at L19 you find 1-5.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Ludgurorf Wodensower</div>
	
