	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />+Stats Potions: These stack with everything. Could follow a &quot;Lesser/Greater&quot; sort of evolution. IE: Lesser Potion of Vitality is +25 HP, and the Greater Potion of Vitality is +75 HP. A gaurenteed hot spot in alchemy if they ever put it live. In addition, this should work with all other statistics. Not too much per potion to prevent overpowering... but really, what tank could resist carrying around a 10-dose potion that adds 20 to STA, or 100 to HP... which stacks with everything? <hr size="1" /></blockquote>~18pp for some marginal stat effects currently. Too expensive. Too marginal effect. Buff slots are prime real estate. Cut the cost in half. Take away the negative effects. <blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Component-Free Utility Potions (Think the current ones require a component...): Levitate, Enduring Breath, Gate. Bind Affinity, and any others I forgot. IMHO, Bind Affinity could be one that requires a lot of extremely rare components and a maximized skill. Gaurenteed seller for tanks tired of running from cities. To sum it up, would revitalize the skill. <hr size="1" /></blockquote>Component free lev and enduring breath are IN GAME. VI discussed bind potions for alchemy before and said no, they didn't want one class to monoplize it... hence sould binders. Gate would rock. But they put it in for pottery, kinda.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Improved Port Potions: Port to a lot of places besides the ones granted. Put in an extremely difficult potion that ports someone to the Nexus from anywhere... and there you go, a hot seller. More locations would not hurt either, besides the 3 or 4 destinations potions are currently limited to. Heck, make potions that drop you at any spire in Norrath! <hr size="1" /></blockquote>As above.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Offensive Potions: Anyone remember UO? Throwing potions at people was always fun. And if that doesn't seem viable, there could be other offensive aid potions. The DS is good, but there should be more. There should be a potion for a combat proc of some sort, perhaps a potion that absorbs melee damage per-hit, a SpellShield style potion, etc. IE: &quot;Potion of Flickering Flame&quot; could give you a chance to proc a fire-based 50DD each hit. <hr size="1" /></blockquote>Doesn't sound like alchemy. Can make proccing weapons in high-end smithing now.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Raising the skill cap for some of the newer potions would be good too (the clarity ones come to mind.) I would personally not open it up to cap at 250 until level 50, though... I've always enjoyed that only the highest-level Shamans can max Alchemy. Should keep it that way. <hr size="1" /></blockquote>No way do i want to spend another fortune getting skill to 250. Sorry.<br />
