	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>OK, I don't read here every thread, so sorry if this is repeated somewhere else, but reading through this thread, I haven't seen anyone bring this view point up.<br />
<br />
Who really knows how to use alchemy?  The shaman that made potion.  Sure some potions should be made for sale...  the less powerful potions, but I also think there should be potions that only shaman can use on themselves or others.  IE. some of you have talked about CH potions. That would be fine and dandy, but I think it should be shaman usable only, and that we could cast it on another char.  Extra HP/AC buff potions could be used in the same maner.  The potions that we can make that are pretty good...  DS, Regen...  Make a version that is just as powerful, cheaper to make, and that can only be used by shaman.  I think this would make me feel much better about getting my alchemy skill up to 180.  I also think that if there were shaman use only potions, you would see a lot more shaman working on their alchemy skill and even possibly working toward that extra AA needed for mastery.<br />
<br />
comments?<br />
<br />
Scrantoon<br />
Oracle<br />
The War Council<br />
Saryrn</p>
	
	
	
	
	
